Louisiana http://ldh.la.gov/index.cfm/page/3518:
As of 3 May 2019, Louisiana has 148 reported cases of HAV infection, 3 of which are not linked to the current outbreak. These are cumulative counts since 1 Jan 2018.

Massachusetts https://www.mass.gov/files/documents/2019/05/06/hav-data-summary-5-3-19.docx:
1 Apr 2018-3 May 2019
Since April 2018, 352 cases of acute hepatitis A virus (HAV) infection have been reported to the Massachusetts Department of Public Health (MDPH) in individuals with recent experience of homelessness, unstable housing, and/or substance use disorder. This report, which is updated weekly, summarizes outbreak-associated cases. Outbreak-associated cases are compared to non-outbreak 2018-2019 cases and 2017 cases (pre-outbreak year).

